stimulus: Hi there! Welcome to the experiment. Press any key to begin.

Before we get started, here is information about consent.

Parent or Guardian: This is a practice round to see whether participants between 5-7 years old understand the study, answer the questions accurately, and stay attentive.

This data will not be used other than for informal interpretation to improve the study design. The participant is welcome to stop whenever, and will always remain anonymous.

The experiment should take no more than 15 minutes.

Do you consent to continuing with the experiment?

Participant: Do you want to play? You are welcome to stop whenever!

Press any key to begin.

In this experiment, we are building a new game!

You will be playing by moving this yellow ball. You want the ball to score in the goal at the top of the screen!

This is your ball!

Press any key to continue.

In the game you will try today, you can move the ball in two different ways. One way you can move the ball is this way, to the left.

If you press this button for the arrow that points this way, to the left, the ball will go this way.

Move this way!

Press the correct button to move the ball this way.

You can also move the ball that way, to the right.

If you press that button on that side, the ball will go that way.

Move that way!

Press the correct button to move the ball that way.

In the game, you want the ball to score in the red goal at the top of the screen here.

When you play, the ball will either be in the blue room or the pink room.

This is what the rooms look like:

This is the Blue Room

This is the Pink Room

Press any key to continue.

Both rooms have an orange wall that can block the ball from scoring in the goal.

If the ball hits the orange wall, the ball won't score in the goal, it will miss.

The orange wall in the Blue Room

The orange wall in the Pink Room

Press any key to continue.

This is what it looks like to score in the blue room, the goal will turn green. Great Job!

Press any key to continue

This is what it looks like to miss in the blue room, the goal will stay red. Uh Oh, no score this time!

Press any key to continue

So if the ball is in the blue room, and you choose this way, the ball will miss. If you choose that way in the blue room, the ball will score.

Press any key to continue

This is what it looks like to score in the pink room, the goal will turn green. Great Job!

Press any key to continue

This is what it looks like to miss in the pink room, the goal will stay red. Uh Oh, no score this time!

Press any key to continue

So if the ball is in the pink room, and you choose this way, the ball will score. If you choose that way in the pink room, the ball will miss.

Press any key to continue

Let's Practice! We will tell you what room you are in, and ask you to either go this way or that way, left or right. Then you can see what happens!

Press any key to continue

You are in the pink room.
Let's  see  what happens if you go that  way!
["video/missthatway.mp4"]

After you see whether the ball scores or misses, you will be asked a question. To pick your answer, choose the arrow button on the same side as the correct response.

If you are asked Remember, your question will ask you to remember which way the ball moved.

If you are asked What if?, your question will ask you to answer what would have happened if that ball had gone the other way.

If you are asked Cause, your question will ask you to answer what caused the ball to score or miss.

Press any key to continue

Nice job! Are you ready to play? Now you get to choose which way the ball will move, but you won't know which room the ball will be in! Try to make the ball score! Do you have any questions?

Press any key to continue
